				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Combat Agility -v- Combat Stability<a name="36850"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 27 04 6:09 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Stability is not a sure thing.  You can still get hit for max, it is not a set % reduction in the damage you take.  Stability is just a % increase to your chance to mitigate incoming damage.  Meanwhile, Agility is a % increase to your chance to completely avoid incoming damage.  Which would you rather increase?  Your chance to take no damage, or your chance to take less damage?  That's what it comes down to.
<br />

<br />
They are both nice skills, Agility is just better.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
